A college professor is working on a long term experiment when a baseball comes through the window destroying all his glassware. The precipitated fluid causes the baseball to be repelled by wood. Suddenly he realizes the possibilities and takes a leave of absence to go to St. Louis to pitch in the big leagues.


IT HAPPENS EVERY SPRING, Writers Valentine Davies and Shirley W. Smith; directed by Lloyd Bacon and released by Twentieth Century Fox.


Starring: Ray Milland, Jean Peters, Paul Douglas, Ed Begley, Ted de Corsia, Ray Collins, Jessie Royce Landis.
